76561198056972440,Recommended,218410,31567990,Posted: 5 May,all,Burnie The Brony,"This is one of my favorite games. And Yes, I've actually played it for hundreds of hours. There was a time when every day while I was winding down I'd put youtube videos on and just play this game, for hours. It's hard to pinpoint what exactly about it is such a draw to me. I think that the gameplay is super satisfying, the story is well-written and actually interesting, and the progression of equipment and levels feels fair and gives you a lot of choices.Beating the game is really only the beginning and throughout your entire first playthrough the game won't be too challenging, your main strategy choice is where to put your archers, which are easily the best class early on. In New Game +, the enemies have various strengths that go beyond just ""more health and damage"" which is nice. Stuff like 50% ranged damage resistance to make you switch up tactics, fading in and out of targetability to make it harder to clump units into a death zone, etc.You also get a new type of reward: in the first playthrough, you accumulate legendary weapons and armor by completing the levels on harder difficulties, which is great but has two issues. They don't feel very unique since it's just high stats, and eventually the stuff you can buy becomes better than the legendary stuff so they're useless. NG+ gives Skulls as a reward for beating higher difficulties that you trade in to upgrade the legendary items, and the upgrades fix both issues. The upgraded legendary items are better stats-wise than the stuff you buy, and they get unique abilities like extra bleed chance, higher crit damage, etc.Another cool thing in NG+ is the addition of several levels where you can only use certain classes, so you might have a level with only berserkers and healers. These levels also introduce a new character who is cool.Basically if you like tower defense games this game is perfect for you, or if you just want a game to relax and wind down with it's been prefect for that for me."
