76561197969749884,Recommended,218410,34403168,Posted: 21 August,all,Sarkoth,"Defender's Quest is not your average Tower Defense game, but what it does, it does really well. It has a nice story, good cartoon art design, whacky characters and a simple to learn yet hard to master core mechanic of tower placements and upgrades as well as about 40 different maps counting all bonus levels and challenges, all of which have an alternate harder version in NG+. Complexity wise it's on the smaller end of the spectrum with only 6 different hero (tower) types and a maximum of 36 towers in total. It also requires to shift heroes (towers) on demand during a map which makes the whole game also a resource management game under great pressure, although it is always possible to completely halt the game while being able to issue commands as well as to up to speed up the game by a whopping factor of 16.All in all: Great accessibility, time well spent and a good game to recommend to fans of the genre."
