76561197970933842,Recommended,218410,8861151,"Posted: 26 January, 2014",all,KaninKanon,"I have always found it really hard to get into the serious RPG game genre like ""Final Fantasy"" and ""Chrono trigger"", not because I dislike the hundreds of hours you have to put into it but the actual combat system have always been booring to me. It gets old way to fast and I get sick of it after a few hours, no matter the great story or character developement I never came back to those games. It was more of a pain and tedious grinding than fun and epic adventure.""Defender's Quest"" however kept me in my seat. It's basically an RPG mixed with tower defense, the best of both worlds if you ask me. I like everyone else play tower defense games because of it's gameplay, which is why this game is great. I took out the part that I hate in RPGs and replaced it with one of the most replayable gametypes that there is, which makes me wonder why no one have come up with this earlier.It seems that alot of games are jumping on the ""Mix RPG with other genres"" train which really makes me happy to see. This game is great from what I've seen so far and great for anyone who have always wanted to get into RPGs but been scared of due to the grindy and difficult gameplay. I have played ""Final Fantasy XIII"" and didn't know what the heck I was doing 15 hours into the game, it felt like a fancy pokemon without the fun. I'm currently only 6 hours in and feel comfortable already,Yes this game is hard and you will have to grind to get the best gear. However, each level has a difficulty setting like any mobile game, making it really easy if you want to speed through the story, still providing a challenge and bonuses for those willing to get them.I am currently only 6 hours in I cant wait to play more, I'm just hoping the game is as lengthy as an actual RPG, which if it isn't might be off putting. And it's worth noting that I only stopped played due to a game crash, it is the first time it has happened so I cannot say if it i a regular.Either way I do sincerely recommend this game, it is currently on sale, definitely worth it for the price tag, grab it now to save some cash."
