76561198060493670,Recommended,218410,8616934,"Posted: 8 January, 2014",all,Moonthirteen,"Tower Defense meets RPG, for real.Many games try to combine different genres yet few does as good a job as Defender's Quest. If you like Tower Defense games and are looking for something new to mix up what is becoming a stale and tired formula, this game is right up your alley. While allowing you to build your characters in the way that you want, customizing your 'towers' becomes a pleasure rather than a chore. The clever use of characters to perform as your towers is a fun way to almost get to know the defenders that you're using, and the story, something that most tower defense games shirk is actually quite amusing. Give it a try if you're wondering what it is about, this game delivers a lot of bang for your buck, offering hours and hours of replayability. The New Game+ feature completely mixes up the challenges so that even when you beat the game you're just getting started."
