,Recommended,218410,8851754,"Posted: 25 January, 2014",all,JKatarn,"Never expected this much from this game.As usual I logged on Steam and found this on sale with just 1.49 USD.Looking at the screenshots it seems like it has some RPG-maker graphics and it is a tower defense game.Man I am really not a fan of tower defense but after scrolling down the review section I see a lot of thumbs up; so I decided to give it a try.And it sucks.... ME IN!The game plays like traditional tower defense, with RPG elements like levelling up, buying armour and upgrading skills.This gives a feeling of progression since in more traditional tower defense game its all about strategy. Every battle is a new battle, nothing carries on to the next level.In this game, your heros are permanent allies. You recruit them from towns, form your own little army and grow them accordingly to your preference.Story wise its ok and the dialogues are funny at times. The presentation of the whole game is quite neat and easy on the eyes so you dont get alot of useless stuff displaying to you.There seems to be quite alot of levels as well as a new game plus where you get unique stuff and enemies which adds replayable value.The only downside is that it seems the skill tree could get some more diversity. Like it would be awesome if a standard warrior can have different styles or something.But all in all this is a solid game and is definitely worth grabbing during this 1.49 USD sale. The fun far exceeds the cost. But if you missed the sale and it goes back to 14.99, I would recommend you to think twice before buying."
