,Recommended,218410,9039408,"Posted: 9 February, 2014",all,LocoPojo,"Tower Defense games are pretty hard to get right - they have to be unique from their predecessors, have a sense of progression, and be mechanically sound throughout, lest they become a boring slog.  I'm pleased to report that Defender's Quest gets it all right.  The characterization of each ""tower"" lends a lot of investment into the game itself, the RPG elements are fun and interesting without breaking the game in half, and the starred progression system meant that I was always seeking - and finding - a new challenge that was scaled to my level.  It's a good story too - simple and filled with pithy dialogue.The best TD I have played - ate days upon days of my time and, oh god, there's a new game plus mode. Halp."
,Recommended,218410,1696436,"Posted: 22 September, 2013",all,Biff Hardjaw,"This game is an excellent blend of light RPG story, character development and Tower Defense gameplay. You take on the role of Azra, who finds herself gifted with a mysterious power to summon beings into a ""halfway"" world where nothing is truly alive or dead. Tasked with escaping a desolate dungeon called ""The Pit"", Azra meets a variety of companions (heroes of different classes) along the way and unravels the mysteries and secrets surrounding the plague that has swept across the land.Upgrade your heroes with class-based skill trees, equipment and boost them up with Azra's magic! This one is definitely a gem, although could use a bit more polish in the graphics department. I enjoyed it thoroughly and advise buying it on sale or with a coupon."
