,Recommended,218410,100812,"Posted: 28 June, 2013",all,demontrace,"Good Tower Defense game, with the ""towers"" being people you find along the storyline, or people you can hire permanently.  You can have up to 6 of each type of tower.  RPG elements mostly revolve around your towers leveling up in a persistant way.  In addition you buy things like weapons and armor for your towers.  Furthermore your main character levels up, who acts as the endpoint of a level, and the person you're trying to protect with your towers.It has the same fallbacks as other TD games, monotony being the main one.  You have to grind out levels and money to make yourself more powerful, but the game has an awesome options menu that gives you the option to speed up exp gain for units in and out of combat, as well as speeding up monetary gain, all without flagging yourself as a cheater, or denying yourself awards.  Shoot one of the higher level achievements even suggests turning on increased exp gain and money gain.Great game."
