76561198028247229,Recommended,218410,3861749,"Posted: 1 July, 2013",all,Reverend Zeratul,"The game describes itself as ""Final Fantasy Tactics meets Tower Defense"" which is actually fairly accurate. It's a tower defense RPG where you gain party members that level up, get new weapons/armor, etc.It also has hints of stuff like Advance Wars and Fire Emblem except your units can't move around the battlefield unless you recall them and send the unit back out in a different position. Lots of replay value with optional side quests, a challenge mode, and the ability to start new games that carry over prior progress with your party.The difficulty settings are highly adjustable so it can be as easy or difficult a game as you want, although the mechanics are fairly basic (it's a tower defense game, they all have the same relative strategy).I don't really think it's worth the full price of $15 and the art style isn't quite to my taste, but it's decent. I got it for $4.95 and it's definitely worth that, at least."
