,Recommended,218410,28574697,"Posted: 23 December, 2016",all,Ktanaqui,"First off, I wholeheartedly recommend this game to anyone who is interested in tower defense style games. A thing to note is that although the description does mention RPG elements, they are very lightly dashed throughout the game and could be attributed to a pretty standard tower defense game. The most RPG-esque element that I can think of after playing through is that every new city you encounter tends to unlock new weapons and armor, which to beat the rest of the game to follow, does require that you purchase. (At least in standard play. There are some specialized modes where this does not hold true.)There is some grinding. Some modes have more grinding than others.There is some frustration; some of the levels are very, very hard. Especially if you're trying to get all of the stars.Actually, I still don't have all of the stars. There are a few levels that are so hard that they seem impossible. (I promise you, they're just very, very hard.)The story is well-written and fun to follow, the levels are pretty varied (especially for a TD game), and the game is, overall, fun."
