76561198058623259,Recommended,218410,33729058,Posted: 22 July,all,remi_sword,"I repurchased this after my original copy had stopped working due to flash/OS compatibility problems. To my delight the it located all my previous save data and let me start where I had left off!The game itself is pretty basic like most tower defense games, you build your army, they stand in one spot, and wreck anything that comes in range of them, all the while trying to keep them from reaching you while managing resources. It does get a little grindy at points where you need to level your troops and fill out character skill tree's, however it's challenge modes offer plenty of opportunity to reduce the mundaneness and speed that process up.One point that makes this game stand out from other TD games is it does have a rather good story, with plenty of character interaction, humor, and dark undertones, and spaces out new troops far enough apart you get more opportunities to play with new setups rather than get everyone within the first half of the game and just try to grind through the rest for more story."
